Job Description:
Job Scope:
 
• Review all incoming invoices for appropriate documentation and approval prior to payment;
• Ensure all payment requests are processed in a timely manner and in accordance to internal approval authority and guidelines;
• Perform accounting entries into ERP system;
• Review and process corporate credit card transaction in Concur;
• Respond to all related vendor inquiries;
• Reconcile vendor statements to Purchase Ledger, including investigating and correcting discrepancies / disputes (if any);
• Prepare monthly bank reconciliations;
• Prepare withholding tax returns;
• Maintain files and documentation thoroughly and accurately, in accordance with company policy and accepted accounting practices;
• Provide support to fellow team members in Accounts Payable activities as needed;
• Assist in maintaining the supplier master and the supplier codes in the accounting system (as required);
• Other ad-hoc duties and projects as assigned.
Job Requirements
• Diploma in Accounting, Finance or equivalent
• At least 3-5  years of relevant working experience
• Basic knowledge and application skills in GST and withholding tax
 
